# Go tooling is LF-only. With core.autocrlf=true (Git-for-Windows system
# default) and no .gitattributes, checkouts rewrote source to CRLF, gofmt then
# flagged whole files, and `git stash` became destructive. Unlike the sibling
# repos whose blobs were already LF, Pulp had CRLF committed into history, so
# this repo also needs a one-time `git add --renormalize .` alongside this file.
#
# eol=lf pins the working tree to LF regardless of core.autocrlf.
*.go   text eol=lf
go.mod text eol=lf
go.sum text eol=lf
*.wit  text eol=lf
*.toml text eol=lf
*.md   text eol=lf
*.sh   text eol=lf
